MultiChoice Nigeria has paid a courtesy visit to the office of the Directors’ Guild of Nigeria (DGN) in its bid to strengthen the ties with the pay-tv company. During the visit, MultiChoice Nigeria reiterated its commitment to the growth of the country’s entertainment industry. Discussions at the meeting revolved around opportunities for collaboration and mutually beneficial ideas with the potential to accelerate the growth of the major industry stakeholder entities such as Africa Magic, MultiChoice Talent Factory and the DGN. The MultiChoice team, led by Caroline Oghuma, Executive Head of Corporate Affairs, explained that the meeting was a sign of the company’s cordial relationship with the DGN and afforded it the opportunity to formally introduce the newly appointed MultiChoice Nigeria’s executives to an important stakeholder group.   K1 will continue to be celebrated for uncommon skills at 65     Dayo Adeneye speaks on Afrobeat Hall of Fame recognition     Ex-BBNaija housemates Teddy A, BamBam welcome second child   President of the DGN, Victor Okhai, commended the company for its effort at reviving its relationship with the guild. “This is a new dawn. The partnership with MultiChoice has been symbolic. It has sold us to the world and amplified and magnified Nollywood even more. “You have helped build capacity over the years and the benefits have been mutual for both parties,” Okhai said. He also urged MultiChoice Nigeria to widen the room for inclusiveness, acquisition and commissioning of content by all and not a select few.